originalText.text: Celeste is an amazing family therapist - let me count the ways. We began seeing her in the throws of adolescence. A 15 and 12 year old respectively, both dyslexic/ADHD and one adopted. Needless to say, a lot going on and she was thoughtful, warm, intelligent, caring, and incredibly insightful about family dynamics. Most importantly, she provided us "the parents" with support and clear direction, not just theories and psycho-babble - which was invaluable. Our kids are thriving, confident and have the tools to deal with the challenges that life will bring. Run don't walk to get on her busy calendar - you won't regret it.
